      "question": "If $3 \\sin \theta + 5 \\cos \theta = 5$, then the value of $5 \\sin \theta - 3 \\cos \theta$ is equal to",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the required value be $x = 5 \\sin \theta - 3 \\cos \theta$.",
          "Square the given equation: $(3 \\sin \theta + 5 \\cos \theta)^2 = 5^2$.",
          "Expand the square: $9 \\sin^2 \theta + 25 \\cos^2 \theta + 30 \\sin \theta \\cos \theta = 25$.",
          "Square the required expression: $x^2 = (5 \\sin \theta - 3 \\cos \theta)^2 = 25 \\sin^2 \theta + 9 \\cos^2 \theta - 30 \\sin \theta \\cos \theta$.",
          "Add the two squared equations: $(3 \\sin \theta + 5 \\cos \theta)^2 + (5 \\sin \theta - 3 \\cos \theta)^2 = 25 + x^2$.",
          "Simplify the sum: $9(\\sin^2 \theta + \\cos^2 \theta) + 25(\\sin^2 \theta + \\cos^2 \theta) = 25 + x^2$.",
          "Since $\\sin^2 \theta + \\cos^2 \theta = 1$, we have $9 + 25 = 25 + x^2$.",
          "Solving for $x^2$: $x^2 = 9$, which implies $x = \\pm 3$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$(3 \\sin \theta + 5 \\cos \theta)^2 + (5 \\sin \theta - 3 \\cos \theta)^2 = 25 + x^2 \\\\ 9 \\sin^2 \theta + 25 \\cos^2 \theta + 30 \\sin \theta \\cos \theta + 25 \\sin^2 \theta + 9 \\cos^2 \theta - 30 \\sin \theta \\cos \theta = 25 + x^2 \\\\ 34(\\sin^2 \theta + \\cos^2 \theta) = 25 + x^2 \\\\ 34(1) = 25 + x^2 \\\\ x^2 = 9 \\\\ x = \\pm 3$"
      },
